This paper deals with the problem of estimating the principal eigenvector of a covariance matrix from streaming data in a distributed setting. This involves techniques from machine learning (estimation of principal components), distributed computing (processing data across multiple nodes), information theory (network communication overhead), and optimization (stochastic algorithms). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
